Nit to be confused with Provencal, Occita nis the Language that was spoken by all of South of France before the Isle-de-France dialect became the official language of France. Thought to be the origin of modern-day Catalan, Gascon is one of 7 dialects of Occitan, which still has 2 million speakers throughout southern france. The language was threatened by educational reforms which meant all Children where instructed in French. Thus Occitan became a spoken language , and after some failed attempts to reintroduce Occitan into schools, the language lives on with no status recognised by the government.